        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(safeguard): resolve compaction provider/model before registering runtime",
        "body": "Fixes #57901.\n\n## Summary\n\nTwo-part fix for the safeguard auto-compaction path ignoring `agents.defaults.compaction.model`:\n\n1. **`extensions.ts`**: `buildEmbeddedExtensionFactories` now reuses the same compaction target resolver as `compaction-runtime-context.ts`, so the safeguard runtime gets the resolved compaction provider/model/auth instead of the active session model.\n2. **`compaction-safeguard.ts`**: swaps precedence in the hook from `ctx.model ?? runtime?.model` to `runtime?.model ?? ctx.model`. Configured compaction model now wins when present; falls back to session model when no override is set.\n\n## Why the previous PR (#57903) wasn't enough\n\nPer the maintainer Codex review on this issue, the explicit `/compact` and context-engine compaction paths were already correct on main. The closed PR #57903 only swapped the precedence in the hook. The remaining bug — and what this PR fixes — is the embedded-extension runtime, which was still being populated with the active session model at registration time. So even with the precedence swap, the safeguard runtime had the wrong `runtime?.model` to compare against.\n\n## Tests\n\n**769 tests pass, 0 errors, 0 failed.**\n\nNew regression: `extensions.test.ts` and `compaction-safeguard.test.ts` cover the case where `ctx.model` = session model (e.g., Opus) and `agents.defaults.compaction.model` = different (e.g., Sonnet). Asserts the configured compaction model wins.\n\nMaintainer review bar (per [comment 4336639752](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/57901#issuecomment-4336639752)) — all four guardrails covered:\n- `/compact` not regressed\n- Context-engine path not regressed\n- Auth-profile dropping when providers change still works\n- No-override fallback (when `agents.defaults.compaction.model` is unset) still falls back to session model\n\n## Stats\n\n- 7 files, +202 / -9\n- CHANGELOG.md updated\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Safeguard auto-compaction was ignoring `agents.defaults.compaction.model`: the embedded-extension runtime was registered with the active session model regardless of any configured compaction override (#57901). This PR makes `buildEmbeddedExtensionFactories` call `resolveSafeguardRuntimeTarget`, which routes through `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget` + `resolveModelWithRegistry`, and flips the precedence in the hook to `runtime?.model ?? ctx.model`. Inline-only models defined under `models.providers.*.models` are honored, and a misconfigured/missing override now triggers a `log.warn(...)` instead of silently registering `model: undefined`.\n\n**Real environment tested:** exe.dev VM, `openclaw/openclaw` fork `joeykrug/openclaw`, worktree at `.../pr-73704-58823/pr-73704`, branch `fix/57901-safeguard-compaction-model` at HEAD `a7e454ae59b3850786ccf15cf9f9e2ec0d779948` (after merging `upstream/main` into the PR branch). Node `v24.15.0`, pnpm `11.1.0`. Sources read live from `src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/extensions.ts`, `src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/compaction-runtime-context.ts`, `src/agents/pi-hooks/compaction-safeguard-runtime.ts`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. `pnpm install --prefer-offline --ignore-scripts` (worktree bootstrap, `SHARP_IGNORE_GLOBAL_LIBVIPS=1`).\n2. Added a standalone real-behavior proof at `scripts/proof/pr-73704-compaction-model.mjs` that imports the actual patched source — `buildEmbeddedExtensionFactories`, `resolveSafeguardRuntimeTarget`, `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget`, and `getCompactionSafeguardRuntime` — and exercises three scenarios end-to-end (no vitest, no mocks of the function under test).\n3. Ran: `node --import tsx scripts/proof/pr-73704-compaction-model.mjs` from the worktree root. Captured terminal output verbatim below.\n4. Also ran the focused regression gates against the merged tree: `pnpm tsgo:core` (EXIT=0), `pnpm tsgo:core:test` (EXIT=0), `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/extensions.test.ts src/agents/pi-hooks/compaction-safeguard.test.ts src/cron/isolated-agent.auth-profile-propagation.test.ts` (Tests: 99 passed across 3 files), `pnpm lint:core` (0 warnings, 0 errors).\n\n**Evidence after fix:** terminal stdout from the live `node --import tsx scripts/proof/pr-73704-compaction-model.mjs` run against the patched source (exit code 0):\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx scripts/proof/pr-73704-compaction-model.mjs\n--- Scenario A: configured compaction model overrides session model ---\n  session provider/model in : anthropic/claude-opus-4-7\n  configured compaction      : anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6 (from agents.defaults.compaction.model)\n  resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget => provider=\"anthropic\" model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n  OK   pure target provider = \"anthropic\"\n  OK   pure target model = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n    modelRegistry.find(\"anthropic\", \"claude-sonnet-4-6\")\n  resolveSafeguardRuntimeTarget => provider=\"anthropic\" modelId=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\" model.id=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n  OK   runtime target provider = \"anthropic\"\n  OK   runtime target modelId = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n  OK   runtime target model.id = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n  OK   runtime target model.provider = \"anthropic\"\n  OK   runtime target model.id is NOT session id = true\n    modelRegistry.find(\"anthropic\", \"claude-sonnet-4-6\")\n  registered safeguard runtime  : provider=\"anthropic\" model.id=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\" contextWindowTokens=200000\n  OK   registered runtime model.id = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n  OK   registered runtime model.provider = \"anthropic\"\n  OK   registered runtime model.id != session model id = true\n\n--- Scenario B: no compaction.model configured -> session model preserved ---\n  registered safeguard runtime  : model.id=\"claude-opus-4-7\" (session id was \"claude-opus-4-7\")\n  OK   session model.id preserved when no override = \"claude-opus-4-7\"\n  OK   registered runtime model is session model (no override) = true\n\n--- Scenario C: configured compaction model missing from registry ---\n[agent/embedded] Configured safeguard compaction model \"anthropic/claude-typo-4-6\" could not be resolved; falling back to the session model.\n  unresolved target             : provider=\"anthropic\" modelId=\"claude-typo-4-6\" model=undefined (safeguard surfaces miss)\n  OK   provider stays as configured = \"anthropic\"\n  OK   modelId stays as configured = \"claude-typo-4-6\"\n  OK   model resolves to undefined on miss = undefined\n\nPROOF PASSED: configured compaction model wins over session model in safeguard registration.\n```\n\nSupplementary CI gates against the merged tree (all green):\n\n```text\n$ pnpm tsgo:core\nEXIT=0  (no diagnostics)\n\n$ pnpm tsgo:core:test\nEXIT=0  (no diagnostics)\n\n$ pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/extensions.test.ts src/agents/pi-hooks/compaction-safeguard.test.ts src/cron/isolated-agent.auth-profile-propagation.test.ts\n Test Files  3 passed (3)\n      Tests  99 passed (99)\n\n$ pnpm lint:core\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** the live `node --import tsx` proof script terminates with `PROOF PASSED` and exit code 0. Scenario A: with `agents.defaults.compaction.model = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"` and session model `anthropic/claude-opus-4-7`, the safeguard runtime registered on the SessionManager carries `model.id = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"` and `model.provider = \"anthropic\"` — the configured compaction model, not the session model. Scenario B: with no override, the safeguard runtime keeps the session model (`claude-opus-4-7`). Scenario C: with a missing/typo override (`anthropic/claude-typo-4-6`), `resolveSafeguardRuntimeTarget` returns `model: undefined`, the runtime carries the configured provider/modelId, and `[agent/embedded] Configured safeguard compaction model ... could not be resolved; falling back to the session model.` is emitted on stderr/stdout. Behavior matches the precedence inverted in `compaction-safeguard.ts` (`const model = runtime?.model ?? ctx.model;`).\n\n**What was not tested:** no live provider API call was made — proof stops at safeguard runtime registration + target resolution against the actual patched source. The end-to-end \"real compaction summary served by the configured model over the wire\" requires a long-running session with an active provider account; that was not run in this VM. The script also does not exercise the `extensions.test.ts` greptile P1 path through vitest (covered separately by the existing test file and the supplementary `pnpm test` run above).\n",
        "branch": "fix/57901-safeguard-compaction-model",
